(23, 1, '2019-09-19 14:42:34', '2019-09-19 14:42:34', '<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 id=\"Introduction\">Introduction</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We want to integrate \"7-zip\" into MS-Windows\' command-line interface. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"objective\"} -->\n<p class=\"objective\">This article helps you download the \"7-zip standalone console version\" and integrate it with MS-Windows command-line interface which enables you to handle compressed file types through \'CMD\' with great flexibility. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 id=\"Prerequisites\">Prerequisites</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here we assume that </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"className\":\"prerequisite\"} -->\n<ol class=\"prerequisite\"><li>You know how to modify the \"PATH\" environment variable. </li><li>You have installed \"7-zip\" or any other archive manager software that supports \'.7z\' files. </li><li> You are familiar with the MS-Windows command-line interface (aka \"cmd\")  and its basic functionalities.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 id=\"Procedure\">Procedure</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Get <a href=\"https://www.7-zip.org/download.html\">the latest version of the application</a>. Look for an item with the description \"7-Zip Extra: standalone console version, 7z DLL, Plugin for Far Manager\" or something similar and click on the corresponding download link. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You\'ll have downloaded a \'.7z\' file which can be extracted if you have already downloaded and installed the standard \"7-zip\" application or any other supporting archive manager software. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Extract the contents of the \'.7z\' file. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can either copy the \'7za.exe\', \'7za.dll\', and \'7zxa.dll\' files into your \"MS-Windows installation directory\" or add the path to the extracted directory to your \'PATH\' environment variable. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Check if you have successfully integrated \"7-zip\" into MS-Windows command-line interface by typing <code>7za</code> into a \"CMD\" window. You should see something like: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"code\"} -->\n<p class=\"code\"><code>7-Zip (a) 19.00 (x64) : Copyright (c) 1999-2018 Igor Pavlov : 2019-02-21</code></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"code\"} -->\n<p class=\"code\"><code>Usage: 7za &lt;command>  [&lt;switches>] &lt;archive_name>  [&lt;file_names>] [@listfile]</code></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"code\"} -->\n<p class=\"code\"><code>&lt;Commands><br>   a : Add files to archive<br>   b : Benchmark<br>   d : Delete files from archive<br>   e : Extract files from archive (without using directory names)<br>   h : Calculate hash values for files<br>   i : Show information about supported formats<br>   l : List contents of archive<br>   rn : Rename files in archive<br>   t : Test integrity of archive<br>   u : Update files to archive<br>   x : eXtract files with full paths</code></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"code\"} -->\n<p class=\"code\"><code>&lt;Switches><br>    -- : Stop switches and @listfile parsing<br>   -ai[r[-|0]]{@listfile|!wildcard} : Include archives<br>   -ax[r[-|0]]{@listfile|!wildcard} : eXclude archives<br>   -ao{a|s|t|u} : set Overwrite mode<br>   -an : disable archive_name field<br>   -bb[0-3] : set output log level<br>   -bd : disable progress indicator<br>   -bs{o|e|p}{0|1|2} : set output stream for output/error/progress line<br>   -bt : show execution time statistics<br>   -i[r[-|0]]{@listfile|!wildcard} : Include filenames<br>   -m{Parameters} : set compression Method<br>     -mmt[N] : set number of CPU threads<br>     -mx[N] : set compression level: -mx1 (fastest)  -mx9 (ultra)<br>   -o{Directory} : set Output directory<br>   -p{Password} : set Password<br>   -r[-|0] : Recurse subdirectories<br>   -sa{a|e|s} : set Archive name mode<br>   -scc{UTF-8|WIN|DOS} : set charset for for console input/output<br>   -scs{UTF-8|UTF-16LE|UTF-16BE|WIN|DOS|{id}} : set charset for list files<br>   -scrc[CRC32|CRC64|SHA1|SHA256|*] : set hash function for x, e, h commands<br>   -sdel : delete files after compression<br>   -seml[.] : send archive by email<br>   -sfx[{name}] : Create SFX archive<br>   -si[{name}] : read data from stdin<br>   -slp : set Large Pages mode<br>   -slt : show technical information for l (List) command<br>   -snh : store hard links as links<br>   -snl : store symbolic links as links<br>   -sni : store NT security information<br>   -sns[-] : store NTFS alternate streams<br>   -so : write data to stdout<br>   -spd : disable wildcard matching for file names<br>   -spe : eliminate duplication of root folder for extract command<br>   -spf : use fully qualified file paths<br>   -ssc[-] : set sensitive case mode<br>   -sse : stop archive creating, if it can\'t open some input file<br>   -ssw : compress shared files<br>   -stl : set archive timestamp from the most recently modified file<br>   -stm{HexMask} : set CPU thread affinity mask (hexadecimal number)<br>   -stx{Type} : exclude archive type<br>   -t{Type} : Set type of archive<br>   -u[-][p#][q#][r#][x#][y#][z#][!newArchiveName] : Update options<br>   -v{Size}[b|k|m|g] : Create volumes<br>   -w[{path}] : assign Work directory. Empty path means a temporary directory<br>   -x[r[-|0]]{@listfile|!wildcard} : eXclude filenames<br>   -y : assume Yes on all queries</code></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 id=\"Summary\">Summary</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"summary\"} -->\n<p class=\"summary\">This guide helps you download the latest \"7-zip standalone console version\" and integrate it into the MS-Windows command-line interface, which enables you to manage compressed files in the command-line interface with great flexibility. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Integrate \"7-zip\" with your MS-Windows command-line interface', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-09-19 14:42:34', '2019-09-19 14:42:34', '', 16, 'http://mywebsite.test/miscellaneous/16-revision-v1-20190919-23/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(24, 1, '2019-09-19 15:30:16', '2019-09-19 15:30:16', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In February 2019, India (as the New Delhi government claimed) responded to a brutal terrorist attack in Pulwama by bombarding what they claimed to be a terrorists\' base in Balakot, Pakistan. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Pakistan was reportedly quick to scramble American F-16 fighter jets to repel the Indian Air Force raid on its soil. Only to realize later that they might have violated some end-user restrictions on using the jets. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/defence/us-seeks-information-on-potential-misuse-of-f-16-by-pakistan/articleshow/68229586.cms\">A report</a> from the Indian Economic Times has only partially elaborated on how the Pakistani Army has trapped itself into an agreement with the US over the purchase of the military equipment which it can\'t use even as means of self-defence.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The report quotes a top US State Department official as saying \"There is a two-man rule, so to speak, for access to this equipment and restricted areas, and F-16 flights outside of Pakistan or participation in exercises and operations with third nations must be approved in advance by the United States government\". </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Meaning that take for example the incident described above, the Pakistani Army had to actually ask for US consent before using F-16s to repel Indian bombers! In other words, by the time the Pakistani Army\'s F-16s would have the permission to take off, if by any luck they did secure the permission, the Indian strikers would have been telling stories of their heroic anti-terrorist operation to their beloved children in bed. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Seriously? Are US-provided fighters so good that can track down perpetrators of an attack to the purchaser\'s unchallenged sovereign territory hours after the attack, while they\'re in bed? </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Why relying on arms from foreign superpowers endangers a nation\'s sovereignty', 'Relying on a foreign superpower for military equipment not only endangers sovereignty, it will also have little effects on improving a nation\'s self-defence. ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'why-relying-on-arms-from-foreign-superpowers-endangers-a-nations-sovereignty', '', '', '2019-09-19 15:41:10', '2019-09-19 15:41:10', '', 0, 'http://mywebsite.test/?p=24', 0, 'post', '', 0),
